<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Niemann Sets Women's World Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Gunda Niemann-Stirnemann of
Germany broke the 3,000-meter world record at the World Speed
Skating Championships in Heerenveen, the Netherlands, on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Niemann clocked in four minutes 5.08 seconds, bettering the
previous record of 4:07.13 set by her compatriot Claudia Pechstein
last December at Hamar, Norway.
</P>
<P>
Niemann picked up pace in the middle laps before accelerating
to the new record in the last two laps with Pechstein skated
4:07.36 for second place in the race.
</P>
<P>
Triple Olympic gold medalist Niemann-Stirnemann, 31, had come
within 0.16 second of Pechstein's mark at the Winter Olympics in
Nagano last month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
