<HEADLINE> UK Unveils 7 Mln Pound Aid Package to Iraqis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Britain announced Saturday plans
to give 7 million pounds (11.7 million U.S. dollars) worth of
humanitarian aid to help relieve the suffering of the people of
Iraq.
</P>
<P>
British International Development Secretary Clare Short said in
a statement that Britain would be channeling the new aid through
food and medicine.
</P>
<P>
She said, "The people of Iraq have suffered too much. We must
do all we can to relieve their suffering."
</P>
<P>
She is to co-host a meeting with Foreign Secretary Robin Cook
to discuss how the European Union can help the United Nations
implement a new oil-for-food scheme. But the time of the meeting
is not known. 
</P>
