<HEADLINE> Dutch Trade Delegation to Visit Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Dutch Minister of Foreign Trade
Anneke van Dok will lead a trade delegation to visit Zimbabwe
next week, the Dutch embassy in Harare said on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The delegation consisting of representatives from 22 Dutch
companies, will stay in Zimbabwe for four days from March 18 to
22 after ending its visit to Botswana, the embassy said in a
statement.
</P>
<P>
The trade mission will explore trade and investment
opportunities in the aviation, transport and distribution,
construction, agriculture, financial and insurance sectors.
</P>
<P>
"The Netherlands has marked Zimbabwe as one of the promising
markets in Africa and the industrial and commercial sectors in
the Netherlands have expressed growing interest in this country,"
the statement noted.
</P>
<P>
During the upcoming visit, van Dok will meet Zimbabwean
President Robert Mugabe and hold talks with Zimbabwean ministers.
</P>
<P>
After concluding its visit to Zimbabwe, the Dutch delegation
will set for Mozambique. 
</P>
</TEXT>
