to the kingdom earlier this month, during which he held wide-scale
talks with Saudi King Fahd Ibn Abdul-Aziz on boosting bilateral
ties and stability in the region.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, the two countries agreed to set up a joint
committee aimed at looking into means to upgrade bilateral
relations.
</P>
<P>
Relations between the two largest Gulf oil producers strained
following the Iranian Islamic revolution in 1979. However,
bilateral ties have been warming up since last year when Iran
started to make initiatives to reconciliate with the Gulf Arab
neighbors.
</P>
<P>
Kharrazi visited Saudi Arabia last November as part of a Gulf
tour to deliver invitations for the Organization of Islamic
Conference (OIC) summit held in Tehran last December.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian foreign minister is scheduled to leave for Doha,
Qatar, Sunday to attend the 25th session of the foreign ministers
of the OIC due for March 15-19. 
