<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, March 14 (Xinhua) -- A man was seriously hurt
Saturday in an explosion in the northern Israeli town of
Afula, Israel Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The report said the explosion occurred suddenly when the
man was examining a cardboard box, which he spotted in a
public park outside the bus station of the town.
</P>
<P>
In the explosion, the man lost both hands and his eyes
were also injured.
</P>
<P>
Police suspected that Palestinian terrorists placed the box
with explosive in the park. Afula is only 10 kilometers away
from the Palestinian city of Jenin, where terrorist cells have
been uncovered in the past.
</P>
<P>
The explosion happened at a time of tense situation in
the territories after three Palestinian workers were shot
death at an Israeli check point near the West Bank city of
Hebron.
</P>
<P>
Following the shooting incident, scores of Palestinians have
been injured in the clashes with Israeli soldiers.
</P>
