<HEADLINE> U.S. Firm Launches Telecommunications Product In Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Polycom, the world's leading
producer of equipment for audio and video conferences, presented a
newly developed product today in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The product, an advanced long-distance audio and video
telecommunications system in the world, introduces the Internet
into the system, which combines the functions of projection,
scanning, annotations and telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
With its 2.5-kilogram video recorder-size view-station, it
enables users to keep focusing on the meetings rather than tuning
the equipment.
</P>
<P>
"China provides a huge potential market for our corporation's
new product, given its daily increasing foreign or domestic
cross-regional business and trade activities," said Jeff Hurmuses,
director-general of the Asia Pacific branch of Polycom today.
</P>
<P>
The corporation's products first entered the Chinese market
last year and constitute a 20 percent market share in the
Asia-Pacific region, he said, adding that the corporation will set
up a representative office in Shanghai by June. 
</P>
</TEXT>
