<DOCNO> XIE19980315.0051 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Portuguese Runner Sets World Record in Lisbon Half Marathon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Antonio Pinto of Portugal set a
world record and won the Lisbon Half-Marathon on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Pinto was timed 59 minutes and 43 seconds over the distance of
21.097 kilometers. The previous world record of 59:47 was set
by Kenyan Moses Tanui in 1993.
</P>
<P>
Pinto, who had placed second four times in the Lisbon event,
broke clear of the field with four kilometers to go.
</P>
<P>
Joseph Kimani of Kenya finished second with a time of 1:00:04.
Zebedayo Bayo of Tanzania came home third at 1:00:26.
</P>
<P>
The women's race was won by Catherina McKiernan of Ireland who
clocked 1:07:50.
</P>
<P>
McKiernan was followed by Cristina Pomacu and Alina Tecuta of
Romania in the second and third places. 
</P>
</TEXT>
