<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Stresses Family Planning, Environmental Protection (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The family planning policy in populous provinces,
poverty-ridden areas and among migrant people should be strictly
carried out, Jiang pointed out.
</P>
<P>
Focusing on education and contraceptive measures, governmental
bodies should combine the policy with enhancing the economy, with
helping people get rich through honest labor and with developing
happy and harmonious families, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Rural areas especially should integrate birth control with
support to poor people, he added.
</P>
<P>
Various local authorities must prevent the environmental and
ecological balance from deteriorating, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Government officials must properly deal with the relationship
between economic development and environmental protection. They
must not sacrifice the environment to short-term economic
increases, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Those serious environmental problems which do great harm to
people must be solved first, he said.
</P>
<P>
Pollution in some river valleys, regions and cities resulting
from harmful industries badly affect local residents' health, he
said. Any excuse for delaying overhauls and shutdowns must not be
considered, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
All localities must ensure that all businesses meet the
national standards for discharging pollutants, although the effort
might be arduous, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was also attended by state leaders such as Li Peng,
Zhu Rongji, Li Ruihuan, Hu Jintao, Wei Jianxing and Li Lanqing.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
