<HEADLINE> More Than 100 Beijing Middle Schools Offer Puberty Classes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 15 (Xinhua) -- More than 100 middle schools in
Beijing have started puberty classes with the help of experts from
Beijing's Family Planning Commission.
</P>
<P>
The class offers students information on sex, physiology and
psychology to help them form knowledgeable concepts of love,
marriage and family, said Liu Zhiyi, headmaster of a middle school.
</P>
<P>
Liu said more than 4,000 students in his school have received
puberty education. His school also has set up a psychological
consulting center.
</P>
<P>
Parents said their children understand more about their
physiological and psychological changes during puberty, and the
relationship between boys and girls are more harmonious.
</P>
<P>
The 13 middle schools in the Dongcheng District have included
puberty education in their research project, and many young
teachers were trained to give puberty classes.
</P>
<P>
Gu Siben, an official with Beijing Education Commission, said
they are encouraging more middle schools to offer puberty
education, and that teachers should be qualified.  
</P>
</TEXT>
