<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Urged to Use Electricity As Main Energy Source </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 15 (Xinhua) -- A lawmaker today urged Beijing to
replace coal with electric power as the main source of energy for
heating and cooking, to put an end to air pollution in the Chinese
capital.
</P>
<P>
Qu Geping, a deputy to the Ninth National People's Congress
(NPC), China's top legislature, in session here since early March,
said Beijing has become one of the world's most polluted
metropolises because of its irrational energy consumption
structure.
</P>
<P>
"Beijing, which burns 30 million tons of coal each year for
heating and gas supply, is one of the top coal consumers in all
capital cities around the world," said Qu, who is also chairman of
the NPC Environment and Resources Protection Committee.
</P>
<P>
Sulphur dioxide and smog released from coal burning have become
major causes of Beijing's worsening air pollution, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, he added, Beijing should fund the construction of a
large thermal power plant in a big coalfield in northwest China's
Shaanxi Province, which will supply clean electricity for
household heating and cooking in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing municipal government has planned to enable one
million local families to use natural gas as main energy by the
year 2000. However, Qu held that China's annual gas resources are
limited and it is impossible to replace all coal consumption with
natural gas.
</P>
<P>
"The annual natural gas supply for Beijing will reach 1.5
billion cubic meters at most, which implies that there is still a
shortage of some 3 million tons," he explained.
</P>
<P>
He proceeded to advocate that all Chinese cities start to promote
the use of unleaded gasoline in local motor vehicles to curb air
pollution caused by auto exhaust emissions.
</P>
<P>
Beijing has banned use of unleaded gasoline since January 1
this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
