<HEADLINE> Serrokh Wins Catalonia Men's Marathon with Race Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, March 15, (Xinhua) -- Moroccan Abdesalam Serrokh
retained his Catalonia marathon title with a new race record in
Barcelona, Spain, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Serrokh, 28, ran most of the race on his own and crossed the
line in two hours nine minutes 48 seconds, beating the previous
best of 2:11:05 set by Dane Allan Zacchariasen 15 years ago.
</P>
<P>
Tanzania's Andrea Nade came second in 2:15:39 while Spaniard
Benito Ojeda was third in 2:15:47.
</P>
<P>
Ana Isabel Alonso of Spain captured the women's title with
2:30:05, improving the course record she set last year by one
second.
</P>
<P>
The second woman across the line was Ethiopia's Elfenesh
Alemu in 2:32:07 while the third place went to her compatriot
Natalia Requena in 2:39:18. 
</P>
