<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NPC Session Receives Record Number of Motions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 15 (Xinhua) -- The ongoing First Session of the
Ninth National People's Congress (NPC), the Chinese parliament,
has received 830 draft motions, a record in NPC history.
</P>
<P>
The draft motions cover the following topics: deepening of
reform, improvement of open policy implementation, promotion of
the rule of law, improvement of the people's congress system,
enhancement of the status of agriculture as the economic base of
the country, acceleration of reform of state-owned enterprises,
the financial system and government structure, establishment of a
social security system, improvement of scientific and
technological development, education, and cultural and ethical
progress.
</P>
<P>
According to NPC regulations, draft motions can be put forth by
an NPC delegation or by 30 NPC deputies jointly.
</P>
<P>
Part of the draft motions, after categorization, will be
submitted to NPC special committees for deliberation as to whether
or not they will become formal motions, and the rest forwarded to
relevant departments and organizations, which are obliged to
handle relevant matters raised in draft motions and inform
deputies of results. 
</P>
</TEXT>
