<HEADLINE> Tibet Marks International Consumers" Rights Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, March 15 (Xinhua) -- The Tibet Autonomous Regional
Bureau for Industry and Commerce received more than 500 complaints
from local consumers during an event here today marking the
International Consumers' Rights Day.
</P>
<P>
This response shows that local consumers are learning to
protect their legitimate rights and interests, an official with
the bureau told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
The official disclosed that the region reported more than 1,400
complaints in the last three years, with an annual increase of 20
percent. More than 4 million yuan was retrieved for 1,200
consumers.
</P>
<P>
The official said that, in the past, local consumers usually
remained silent when they bought cheap, fake and shoddy goods,
attributing this to low purchasing power.
</P>
<P>
Currently, complaints raised by local consumers cover not only
big commodities, but also small ones.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, local industrial and commercial bureaus and
technical supervision departments have annually strengthened
publicity about related laws on March 15, International Consumers'
Rights Day.
</P>
<P>
This year, the region established 42 complaint stations and
publicized 120,000 copies of related materials.
</P>
<P>
An association for the protection of the rights and interests
of local consumers is scheduled to be established soon, the
official said.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
