<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 15 (Xinhua) -- More than 10,000
community-spirited civil servants from over 90 departments and
bureaus of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) took
part in a walk-for-a-million here Sunday to raise funds for the
Hong Kong Community Chest.
</P>
<P>
The Civil Service Walk for Charity, which commemorates the 30th
 Anniversary of the chest, was the first of its kind since the
establishment of the SAR government on July 1, 1997.
</P>
<P>
The 7.5-km walk, which started at the Sha Tin Park Main Plaza,
was officiated by SAR Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa, who is
president of the Hong Kong Community Chest, and his wife Betty
Tung Chiu Hung-ping, and Administrative Secretary of the SAR
government Anson Chan.
</P>
<P>
A lion dance from the Fire Services Department led the
officiating guests and other senior government officials,
including Justice Secretary Elsie Leung Oi-sie, to the Lek Yuen
Bridge to mark the beginning of the walk touring round the Shing
Mun River Channel in Sha Tin, Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Walkers also enjoyed live band performances by the Hong Kong
Police, the Correctional Services Department, Auxiliary Medical
Service and the Civil Aid Service respectively at various
locations throughout the route.
</P>
<P>
The walk lasted for about two hours till a light rain
fell. 
