<HEADLINE> New Male Contraception Device Developed in Xi'an </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, March 15 (Xinhua) -- A new kind of male contraception
gadget which tends to be easily accepted by men of various
cultural backgrounds has been developed in Xi'an, provincial
capital of northwest China's Shaanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
The new invention has been granted state patent rights for
practical technologies, and the products are soon to be
available. The functioning of the new device, which is as big as a
beeper, is achieved through changing the habitat of sperm to stop
spawning or lead to the quick termination of new ones, said Yang
Xiyong, the device's inventor.
</P>
<P>
The gadget can be placed in the users' underwear, where it
transmits pulses into the body to autonomic nerves which change
the sperm's habitat.
</P>
<P>
Clinical researchers have found the new gadget convenient to
use and, while functioning, it is safe, reliable and reversible.
</P>
<P>
One hour of use ensures one month's successful contraception,
researchers said, and a man can restore his reproductive
capability two months after halting the gadget's use. 
</P>
</TEXT>
