<HEADLINE> Northern Chinese City To Hold Relics Exhibition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, March 15 (Xinhua) -- China's largest display of relics
and works of art will be held on May 16 in the northern port city
of Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition will display more than 10,000 relics from
stores, markets, and individuals across the country.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition is expected to attract overseas antique dealers
and collectors and a Tianjin relics company will set up a panel of
experts to appraise pieces to help keep fakes out of the fair.
</P>
<P>
A series of works by famous Chinese artists like Qi Baishi,
Zhang Daqian, and Huang Binhong will be on display along with
works of porcelain, jade, wood, and metal.
</P>
<P>
Some 184 important relics will be auctioned off, mainly
porcelain from the Qing Dynasty (1644-1911) and paintings from
modern times.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
