<HEADLINE> Northwest China Province Helping Poverty-Stricken Workers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Gansu Province
raised 10.45 million yuan to help poverty-stricken workers at the
beginning of this year.
</P>
<P>
Extending a helping hand to laid-off or impoverished workers is
at the top of the provincial government's agenda, which is of
vital importance to the country's reform, development and
stability, officials said.
</P>
<P>
Financial and labor departments in Gansu have allocated 23
million yuan to set up re-employment funds at the provincial
level. Other local governments have collected 85.19 million yuan
in relief funds.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government also extended pension and
unemployment insurance to 2.2 million people.
</P>
<P>
Apart from financial aid, Gansu has established more than 1,800
agencies to help laid-off workers in seeking new jobs. Thirty
re-employment markets opened in cities like Lanzhou, Tianshui, and
Baiyin to help more than 10,000 laid-off workers find jobs.
</P>
<P>
Gansu has set up 122 re-employment service centers to help
laid-off workers from financially troubled enterprises. About
98,000 laid-off workers have found jobs, and the re-employment
rate is at 50 percent in the province.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
