<HEADLINE> Pudong Announces New Plans to Attract Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 15 (Xinhua) -- The Pudong New Area of Shanghai
has come up with new investment plans this year and expects to use
about 1.5 billion US dollars worth of overseas spending, a third
of Shanghai's total, and 300 million yuan from domestic investors.
</P>
<P>
The majority will be spent on information technology,
automobile, pharmaceutical, new materials, and modern agriculture
projects.
</P>
<P>
Local government organizations like the municipal overseas
investment committee and foreign economic and trade committee, and
big markets and enterprises of metals, commodity, and technology
exchanges, will be re-located from downtown Shanghai to the Pudong
New Area this year.
</P>
<P>
A group of companies will be set up in the area to be listed on
the Shanghai Stock Exchange after it moves to Pudong. And, 15 of
the world's top 500 multinationals and 20 of the 500 biggest
Chinese companies are expected to invest in the area, while 40
overseas-funded companies in the area are expected to increase
their investment a great deal this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
