<HEADLINE> Yunnan Prepares for World Gardening Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Yunnan
Province is preparing for the 1999 World Gardening Fair, which is
to be held in Kunming.
</P>
<P>
An official with the Yunnan Gardening Bureau told participants
at an international tourism fare here that more than 60 countries
have expressed their intention of attending the fair, including
Japan, France, and Sweden.
</P>
<P>
The fair covers an area of 218 hectares in a suburb of Kunming,
the provincial capital, he said, and the provincial government is
devoting considerable effort to build nine exhibition halls and
gardening centers.
</P>
<P>
The event is China's last scheduled major international fair of
this century, he added.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the province attracted 23.7 million tourists,
805,400 from foreign countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
