<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italian President in Hospital for Heart Checkup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 14 (Xinhua) - Italian President Oscar Luigi
Scalfaro was hospitalized Saturday evening for a heart checkup,
the president's office announced in a statement.
</P>
<P>
Scalfaro, 79, entered Rome's Gemelli hospital because of "the
after-effects of a bout of influenza," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
His health condition does not seem to be serious as reports
here said he walked to the hospital "on his own feet."
</P>
<P>
On March 11, aides announced cancellation of all Scalfaro's
public engagements for at least a week, citing persisting "flu
symptoms and doctor's recommendations."
</P>
<P>
He canceled a trip to Israel and Syria, originally scheduled
for March 15-20.
</P>
<P>
The flu had also forced him to cancel a state visit to China at
the end of last month.
</P>
<P>
Hospital sources said the Italian president will stay at the
Gemelli for a few days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
