<HEADLINE> 25 Killed, 41 injured in Fighting in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, March 15 (Xinhua) -- At Least 18 Tamil rebels and
seven Sri Lankan Army soldiers were killed and 41 soldiers injured
Saturday in fighting in Mankulam, Northern Province, a military
release here said Sunday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The release said advancing government troops who are carrying
on the operation "Jaya Sikuru" (Sure of Victory), confronted a
group of rebels and engaged them with small arms and machine guns,
killing at least 18 rebels and causing heavy casualties among the
rebels. The troops captured a rebel bunker by Saturday noon.
</P>
<P>
Four soldiers are reported to the missing in action, the
release added.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been waging a 15-year war in the north
and east of the country in their bid to set up a separate Tamil
state.
</P>
<P>
The government troops launched the Jaya Sikuru offensive in May
last year in a bid to recapture 75 km of the main highway from
Vavuniya to Jaffna Peninsula which runs through the rebel-held
territory. 
