<HEADLINE> "Titanic" Surpasses "Star War" as Top-Selling Movie </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles, March 14 (Xinhua) -- "Titanic" surpassed "Star War"
Saturday evening as the top domestic money-earner of all time,
according to a Hollywood spokesman.
</P>
<P>
"Without a doubt we passed the record today," said Blaise Noto,
spokesman for Paramount, which co-produced the 200-million-dollar
film with the 20th Century Fox.
</P>
<P>
Going into Saturday, the shipreck saga claimed receipts of
458.2 million dollars and was projected by industry estimates to
have grossed at least 7 million dollars more by Saturday
evening. This gave it a total of more than 465 million dollars,
thus breaking the all-time domestic mark of 461 million dollars
set by "Star War".
</P>
<P>
U.S. film industry experts pointed out that it took five
re-release for "Star War" to make that kind of money, while
"Titanic" is steaming in the same direction on its first time out.
</P>
<P>
Worldwide, "Titanic" already holds the record for returns with
receipts in excess of $1.1 billion.
</P>
<P>
"Titanic" has been the nation's No.1 film for 12 straight weeks
and Hollywood experts estimate it will hold that position for at
least next two weeks since another highly publicized movie
"Primary Colors" opens in a week.
</P>
<P>
But if "Titanic" wins the best picture Oscar at March 23's
Academy Awards, the experts believe, it will continue to be the
No.1 film for much longer period in the United States. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
