<HEADLINE> Business Increase In Shanghai Free Trade Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai's Waigaoqiao Free Trade
Zone expects a 20 percent increase in its GDP this year, from the
nearly six billion yuan last year, and an industrial output
increase of 30 percent, from last year's 6.4 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Waigaoqiao port handled 490,000 standard containers last year,
up 150,000 from the 1996 figure, and it is expected to rise to
600,000 this year. The port ranks second in China after Shanghai
in terms of container business.
</P>
<P>
The zone plans to have 350 million US dollars worth of overseas
investment this year in 300 new overseas-funded projects. By the
end of February, the zone had 2,100 overseas-funded projects,
involving nearly 2.9 billion US dollars in total investment.
</P>
<P>
The zone did 2.7 billion US dollars worth of foreign trade in
1997, over 700 million US dollars of which was in exports, more
than two times the 1996 figure.
</P>
<P>
Industrial output value in the zone rose 125 percent over 1996
to 6.4 billion yuan last year, as a result of the speedy
development of the processing trade.
</P>
<P>
There are now 39 multinationals investing in the processing
trade in the zone, with 81 companies involved in the business.
</P>
</TEXT>
