<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambian Govt Has No Money for Fertilizer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, March 15 (Xinhua) -- The Zambian government has said
that it has no money this year to buy fertilizer for farmers,
Sunday Mail reported.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted Agriculture, Food and Fisheries Minister
Edith Nawakwi as saying in central province Sunday that
fertilizer for maize will not be available to the farmers because
the government has no money to buy it.
</P>
<P>
She said the government has not budgeted for fertilizer this
year and as such farmers should not expect any from her ministry.
</P>
<P>
She told the farmers to be ready for the consequences of the
situation.
</P>
<P>
The minister urged the farmers to invest in livestock which if
looked after well could bring development and raise their
standard of living.
</P>
<P>
Nawakwi said the government is ready to help farmers who will
diversify into ranching from maize farming.
</P>
<P>
Money is available under the rural investment fund for farmers
to start other projects other than maize farming, she noted.
</P>
<P>
Last year the country's agricultural production decreased by
3.4 percent due to deferred supply of fertilizer input among
others. 
</P>
</TEXT>
