<HEADLINE> HK Lawmaker Urges Laid-Off Workers to Adapt to Social Needs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 15 (Xinhua) -- A prestigious Hong Kong
businessman today proposed that laid-off workers of China's
state-owned enterprises adapt themselves to the needs of the
society for the sake of their re-employment at an earlier date.
</P>
<P>
"According to the laws that guide the flow of human resources,
layoff quite possibly marks a new fresh beginning for the
laborers," said Wilfred Wong Ying-wai, a deputy from the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (SAR) to the Ninth National People's
Congress, China's top legislature, in session here since early
March.
</P>
<P>
Wong, who is also president of Hong Kong-based China Industries
Investment Group, said that he quite understands the feelings of
frustrations and unsafety shared by many laid-off workers and has
much compassion on them.
</P>
<P>
"Therefore, I's like to give them a sincere advice, that is,
regarding yourselves as part of the human resources of the
society, making adjustments according to social demand, tapping
your potentials and further increasing your competence, and you
will have bright prospects," he said.
</P>
<P>
Wong has long been impressed by the abundant human resources
and highly-competent skilled personnel in the interior areas,
where he has made a lot of investments, he noted.
</P>
<P>
However, he added, both the governments and individuals in the
interior are still not adequately aware of the importance of
market demand in the distribution of human resources, resulting in
an increasing waste of manpower and skilled personnel.
</P>
<P>
"So it is essential not only for government officials and
business managers, but for every individual laborer, to become
market-oriented on the issue of employment," he said.
</P>
<P>
While trying to take care of and help re-train laid-off
workers, he suggested that the government should also take prompt
and effective measures to cultivate and develop a mature human
resources market across the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
