<HEADLINE> Top PLA Officer Speaks About Future Military Work (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Issue No.6 of the biweekly
magazine "Seeking Truth," which comes out on March 16, carries an
article by General Fu Quanyou, chief of General Staff of the PLA,
on improving the country's military work.
</P>
<P>
The article contains four parts: arming oneself with scientific
theories and high-tech knowledge; increasing military reforms;
building quality in the military; and administration in strict
accordance with the law.
</P>
<P>
Fu says that study is a Party tradition and a prerequisite and
a base for developing the cause and quotes the speech by Jiang
Zemin, General Secretary of the Communist Party of China (CPC)
Central Committee, where he emphasizes that the times, the
situation, and the cause call for study, and it is a powerful
driving force for future development of the army.
</P>
<P>
Fu also emphasizes Maxism-Leninism, Mao Zedong Thought, and
Deng Xiaoping Theory. Deng's theory serves as a guide for the
realization of socialist modernization during reforms, he says,
and there can be no other theory because his is a combination of
Marxism for contemporary practice in China with Chinese
characteristics. It can solve problems related to the future of
socialism and is the only theory which can solve problems of
modernization in the military.
</P>
<P>
Fu also points to the importance of agreeing with the CPC
Central Committee with Comrade Jiang Zemin at the core and the
Central Military Commission, under any and all circumstances.
</P>
<P>
He urges the whole army to study high-tech so as to improve the
military through science and technology.
</P>
</TEXT>
