<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 12 Kenyans Killed in Road Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, March 15 (Xinhua) -- At least 12 people died and
eight seriously injured Saturday when the bus they were traveling
in rolled several times at Samburu on the Nairobi-Mombasa
highway, a daily paper reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Coast provincial police boss Japheth Mwania who visited the
scene, confirmed that 10 people died on the spot and two others
died while being treated at a nearby hospital.
</P>
<P>
The East African Standard newspaper said the death toll has
reached 14 while more than 10 people were critically injured and
another 16 suffered minor injuries.
</P>
<P>
The bus, traveling from Nairobi to Mombasa, skidded and rolled
for more than 300 meters at about 7:00 a.m. Some of its survivors
remained trapped in the wreckage for more than five hours --
until 11 a.m. when police from Mombasa came to their aid.
</P>
<P>
Among the survivors were the driver identified as Julius
Ndambuki and an eight-month-old baby whose mother died in the
crash. The total number of the passengers in the bus is 53.
</P>
<P>
Ndambuki said the accident occurred when he lost control of
the vehicle as he tried to avoid a head-on collision with a
truck.
</P>
<P>
"I came out of a bend only to find myself face-to-face with a
lorry which was overtaking. As I was trying to avoid it, the bus
veered off the road and began rolling," he said. His head and
left leg were bandaged.
</P>
<P>
Witnesses said the bus rolled three times before landing in a
ditch.
</P>
<P>
On the same day, more than 60 passengers were injured in
another road accident along the Nairobi-Nakuru highway, 10 of
them seriously.
</P>
<P>
The tragedy occurred shortly before noon when a bus hit a
small pick-up, lost control and overturned. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980315.0139 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Top PLA Officer Speaks About Future Military Work (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fu quotes CPC Central Committee General Secretary Jiang Zemin
as saying in his report to the Party's 15th National Congress that
China should place importance on building the military with
science and technology, and improving its defensive warfare
capability with modern technology. China should train capable
people and try hard to improve leaders and soldiers' scientific
and cultural awareness.
</P>
<P>
Fu says technology seems to be developed by technological
competition, but actually it is decided by competing human
resources and we should be more aware of the decisive role human
resources play in the quality of a military force and improve the
training of humans, attracting more excellent youths with at least
a high school education or college graduates.
</P>
<P>
He says the nation's military concentrates on economic
development, requiring human, material, and financial resources
for key projects, but we should push the modernization drive of
armaments forward.
</P>
<P>
China cannot catch up with the advanced world levels simply by
introducing foreign armaments, he says. It should develop hi-tech
weapons of its own through a combination of development and
renovations.
</P>
<P>
The army's automatic command system should improve efficiency,
providing a solid base for both scientific and efficient decision
making, he notes.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980315.0140 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Top PLA Officer Speaks About Future Military Work (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fu says the PLA must carry out Jiang Zemin's orders to study
the characteristics and laws of management, military struggles,
and national defense, and that in the new historical period, the
army must pay attention to two things: technology on the
battlefield and the progress of reforms, opening-up, and the
socialist market economy.
</P>
<P>
With the extensive application of the latest technology,
especially information technology, to the military, future wars
will be fought with technology in weapons and command.
</P>
<P>
And, because the PLA forces are not up to date in concepts of
war, staff qualifications, and weapons, this is a serious
challenge for military reforms, he says.
</P>
<P>
The reforms, opening-up, and socialist market economy have
breathed new life into the military, but have also brought
problems. Some PLA policies lag behind the market economic
developments, making reforming the troops even more necessary, he
says.
</P>
<P>
The laws of military management in relation to military reforms
is a profound revolution in the military, he says, and some old
concepts are hindering the reforms, and urges the soldiers to
change their ideas under the guideline of Mao Zedong Thought, Deng
Xiaoping Theory, and Jiang Zemin's instructions on army work,
while absorbing useful ideas from elsewhere.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980315.0141 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Top PLA Officer Speaks About Future Military Work (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fu stresses that a major part of military work is administering
the army in accordance with the law and standardizing the
military. The military in the new era needs a high-degree of
standardization and steps should be taken to do this.
</P>
<P>
If the military is not run in strict accordance with the law, a
slip of the hand and the push of a button could mean defeat or
lead to destruction, he says.
</P>
<P>
It is important that we catch up with global military
developments, administer the military in accordance with the law,
and standardize the military in case of future wars, which will
combine sea, air, and land battles by electronic means, requiring
perfect coordination, he stresses.
</P>
<P>
In future, high-tech wars could erupt suddenly and require
various operations and a high degree of combat readiness and quick
reaction, Fu notes.
</P>
<P>
He says that from now to the mid-21st century will be an
important period of national defense and military development, so
the military should rally more closely around the CPC Central
Committee with Jiang Zemin at the core, hold the banner of Deng
Xiaoping Theory high, and build the military into a strong,
modern, and standardized force. 
</P>
</TEXT>
