<HEADLINE> Son Soubert Becomes Cambodia's Son Sann Party President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Son Soubert, first vice
president of his faction of the Khmer Buddhist Liberal Democratic
Party (KBLDP), replaced his father, Son Sann, as president of the
party on Saturday, Rasmei Kampuchea daily reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The party was also renamed as Son Sann Party.
</P>
<P>
Son Sann resigned as president of his faction of the KBLDP soon
after he returned to Phnom Penh on Wednesday so as to take up his
position in the proposed Constitutional Council.
</P>
<P>
Thach Reng and Kem Sokha, parliament members of the party,
became vice presidents.
</P>
<P>
As new party president, Son Soubert said, he will do his best
to realize the party's goal to build Cambodia into a free,
democratic, neutral and nonaligned nation.
</P>
<P>
His father, Son Sann, said the change of name will benefit the
party to win more supporters in the general elections scheduled
for July 26, but the party will not change its political target.
</P>
<P>
The party decided to change its name after a protracted battle
with rival faction leader Ieng Muly, who was also attempting to
register for the elections under the same name.  
</P>
