<HEADLINE> Albanian Parliament Adopts Privatization Law </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The Albanian People's Assembly, or
parliament, approved a law Saturday to open up the country's key
economic sectors to the privatization process.
</P>
<P>
The law provides guidelines for privatizing the power, mining,
oil and gas, communications, forestry, air and rail service
industries as well as other infrastructure facilities.
</P>
<P>
The financial sector is also subject to the mandate, which is
termed by Minister of Economy and Privatization Ylli Bufi as of a
high significance to the country's future economic development.
</P>
<P>
Under the new law, private fund should account for at least 30
percent of the total investment in a privatization project, and
the government should alleviate social pains of the process.
</P>
