<HEADLINE> Crimes Drop in Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Nearly 2.4 million criminal
offences were registered in Russia in 1997, a drop of nine percent
over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Criminal offences in major cities such as Moscow declined by as
much as 20 percent, according to a recent report by Interior
Minister Anatoly Kulikov.
</P>
<P>
The report said that last year also saw a sharp increase in
solving crimes of serious nature.
</P>
<P>
As many as 132 paid murders were cracked in 1997, which doubled
the number of such cases solved in the previous year.
</P>
<P>
However, the report said that criminal offences, which often
involve mafia, weapons and explosives, are becoming more organized
and dangerous.
</P>
<P>
A total of 426 policemen died and 2,200 others were injured at
their posts last year, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
