<HEADLINE> Czech Republic, Russia to Further Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The Czech Republic and Russia have
signed a series of documents on substantiating their economic and
trade relations with specific cooperation projects.
</P>
<P>
The documents, in the form of memos and agreements from the
meeting here on March 12-14 of a joint commission, cover
transportation, energy and inter-governmental cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The Czech-Russian Economic and Technological Cooperation
Commission agreed to further develop the two countries' trade and
economic relations on the basis of equality and mutual benefit.
</P>
<P>
As follow-ups to the meeting, the fourth of the kind, the two
sides worked out 15 joint projects ranging from exploration of oil
and gas to science and technological cooperation. 
