<HEADLINE> Earthquake Hits Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 15 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 7.4 on
the Richter scale hit Iran at 03:40 (Beijing time) today,
according to the monitoring by China's State Seismological Network.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter was located at 30.6 degrees north latitude and
57.8 degrees east longitude.
</P>
<P>
No other details were available.
</P>
<P>
The open-ended Richter scale measures the total energy released
by an earthquake, as indicated by ground motion recorded on
seismographs.
</P>
<P>
Every increase of one digit in the scale represents a tenfold
increase in the magnitude of the earthquake. A quake registering 6
on the scale is capable of causing severe damage in populated
areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
