<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rusedski Enters Final in Champions Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Greg Rusedski clocked the
fastest serve ever on the ATP Tour as he powered his way into the
final of the Champions' Cup in Indian Wells, California on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The sixth-seeded Briton recorded a 7-6 (7/5), 6-1 win over
Austria's former world No. 1 Thomas Muster, securing his final
spot against either seventh-seeded Chilean Marcelo Rios or
American new comer Jan-Michael Gambill.
</P>
<P>
Rusedski slammed down a 239.8-km effort in the 11th game of the
first set, the fastest serve ever recorded in the ATP tournament.
</P>
<P>
As always, Rusedski said he was more pleased with his victory
than with the record, saying "If I would have hit 149 and lost
the match, I would be very disappointed."
</P>
<P>
Rusedski overpowered on his serve, putting 73 percent of his
first serves in play and winning 33 of 36 first serve points.
</P>
<P>
He lost only three points on his serve in the first set and
only four points in the second as he stormed into his first-ever
final of a 'Super Nine' event. 
</P>
</TEXT>
