<DOCNO> XIE19980315.0181 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tyre Sector Faces Tough Challenges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Tariff cuts, cancellation of the
consumption tax and favorable loans are needed soon to maintain
the viability and profitability of domestic tyre producers, say
industry insiders.
</P>
<P>
"Tariff rates of 20 percent on rubber imports, 10 percent
consumption tax on tyre sales plus repayments of heavy bank loans
are imposing amounting pressure on domestic tyre producers," Ju
Hongzhen, vice-president of the China United Rubber Corp, said in
today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
Ju warned that the state tyre manufacturers would see their
market share shrink significantly if the central government takes
no measures to help them.
</P>
<P>
"At the end of the century, as much as 80 percent of the market
for radial tyres used for cars is expected to be in the hands of
the foreign-funded ventures," Ju said.
</P>
<P>
The paper reported that at present, there are at least 30
foreign-funded tyre producers in China.
</P>
<P>
Ju gave an advice for domestic enterprises to develop radial
tyres used by heavy-duty trucks, and for bias tyre producers to
increase product variety and improve quality to keep competitive.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, the output of motor vehicles used for transportation
in rural areas hit 2.6 million, "spawning an enormous market for
Medium-sized or small tyre producers," Ju said.
</P>
<P>
Xie Mingzhi, an expert with the Nanfang Rubber Group Corp, said
stimulus is also urgently needed to boost tyre exports, which have
yet to be seriously hurt by the financial turmoil in Southeast
Asia.
</P>
<P>
"Overcapacity in the domestic market and appreciation of the
renminbi would mean tough times ahead for tyre exporters," Xie
said.
</P>
<P>
Over the past few years, China has exported about 6.5 million
tyres annually on average, accounting for 10 to 15 percent of its
total output. Southeast Asia, the Middle East and Africa are the
major destinations of tyre shipments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
