<HEADLINE> Tchmil Wins Stage, Vandenbroucke Retains Lead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Belgium's Andrei Tchmil clinched
his second consecutive stage victory in the Paris-Nice cycle race
on Saturday as the classic reached the Mediterranean coast of
Cannes.
</P>
<P>
Compatriot Franck Vandenbroucke still retained his lead by 40
seconds, suggesting his momentum for the title on the eve of the
race's eighth and final stage.
</P>
<P>
Russian-born Tchmil won the sixth stage in Sisteron on Friday
and outsprinted Frenchman Stephane Barthe and holder Laurent
Jalabert in a dash to the line in Cannes.
</P>
<P>
In the 223 kilometer route, the 35-year-old broke away in the
last 100 meters to clinch his fourth success this season.
</P>
<P>
Vandenbroucke lead three-time winner Jalabert by 40 seconds
before the ultimate stage, 161.4 km around Nice on Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
