<HEADLINE> U.S. Draws Paraguay 2-2 in Soccer Friendly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The United States national
soccer team levelled with Paraguay 2-2 on Saturday in a friendly
game at San Diego, California as both squads were tuning up for
the World Cup finals to be started in June in France.
</P>
<P>
In the afternoon match, Paraguay opened the scoring in the 15th
minute when Denis Camiza's low shot off a right-side back pass
beat American goalkeeper Juergen Sommer.
</P>
<P>
American Chad Deering hit the first equaliser in the 21st
minute, heading in Eric Wynalda's well-executed curving corner
kick from the right wing.
</P>
<P>
In the 50th minute, the United States overtook a 2-1 lead when
San Diego native Marcelo Balboa scored from near the penalty spot
with a diving header from almost ground level off a left-side
cross from Alexi Lalas.
</P>
<P>
However, the advantage was soon be wiped out when American
goalkeeper Juergen Sommer committed an unnecessary foul inside the
box in the 75th minute to award Paraguay a penalty kick.
Francisco Arce converted with a powerful, high blast to score the
last.
</P>
<P>
After the draw, the United States held three wins against four
draws and one loss this year while Paraguay had its first draw
after a win over Poland in February. 
</P>
</TEXT>
