<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Bulgarian striker Hristo Stoichkov
has left Barcelona to nullify his contract which would run to June
30, club officials confirmed on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The club had cancelled the contract of 32-year-old Stoichkov
"by mutual consent", the officials said.
</P>
<P>
Stoichkov, the 1994 European Player of the Year, had been at
Barcelona for seven of the last eight seasons and was part of the
side which won the 1992 European Cup.
</P>
<P>
Stoichkov had been unhappy at the club since Dutch coach Louis
van Gaal took over last summer.
</P>
<P>
The pair have clashed frequently and the final straw for van
Gaal came last week when Stoichkov travelled to Argentina without
club permission to play in a friendly international. 
