Cooperation said that in 1997 China's exports to the region hit
4.6 billion US dollars, or up 47.7 percent from the previous
year. Imports from Latin America also went up, he said.
</P>
<P>
This is a great achievement for China, which ahs been trying
since 1990 to diversify its export markets, which are currently
concentrated in Asia, North America and Western Europe.
</P>
<P>
