<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hingis Wins Evert Cup in California </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Martina Hingis of
Switzerland defeated second-seeded American Lindsay Davenport 6-3,
6-4 on Saturday to win the 1.25 million U.S. dollars Evert Cup
tennis championship held at Indian Wells, California.
</P>
<P>
Hingis captured her second title of the year by winning the
battle between the world's top two players. She earned 205,000
dollars for the victory as she wrapped up her 16th career singles
title.
</P>
<P>
It was Hingis' second revenge match in two days. On Friday,
she eliminated, at the semifinals, eighth-seeded American teenager
Venus Williams, who beat the top-ranked player in January. Last
month, Davenport sent Hingis to her second loss of the season in
the final of the Pan Pacific Open in Tokyo.
</P>
<P>
Hingis improved to 15-2 this season and 6-4 lifetime against
Davenport. Earlier this year, she captured her fourth Grand Slam
title in two years at the Australian Open. Hingis finished last
season with 12 singles titles overall, including three Grand Slam
titles.
</P>
<P>
Davenport, 21, who lost for only the fourth time in 20 matches
this season, failed to reap her 15th career singles title. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
