<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Niemann-Stirnemann Breaks World Speedskating Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEERENVEEN, Netherlands, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Defending world
champion Gunda Niemann-Stirnemann of Germany shattered on Saturday
women's 3,000-meter speedskating world record.
</P>
<P>
She clocked 4 minutes 5.08 seconds during a race of the current
World All-Round Speedskating Championships.
</P>
<P>
The previous mark was 4:07.13 held by another German skater
Claudia Pechstein since the Hamar World Cup race.
</P>
<P>
This is the first world record to fall at this year's
Heerenveen championships. Yet both men's and women's race
leaders, Ids Postma of the Netherlands and Niemann-Stirnemann, are
likely to better the listed world records for the all-round
speedskating events. 
</P>
</TEXT>
