<HEADLINE> Santiago Promoting Electric Cars, Bicycles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The Chilean capital of Santiago
is promoting the use of electric cars and bicycles as alternatives
to conventional fuel-powered automobiles.
</P>
<P>
As part of an experiment, three electric cars and two electric
bicycles started from Saturday moving around the city's streets
and parks, and would be there for 30 and 60 days.
</P>
<P>
"We want to call for a public bidding to put into operation
more electric cars and also bicycles after we see the results in
the practice," Santiago Mayor Jaime Cavinet told the press.
</P>
<P>
Electricity-powered vehicles are environmental friendly, as
they emit no pollutants into the air. And the technology is
vigorously pursued in the United States and European nations.
</P>
<P>
In Santiago's case, the electric cars are provided by the Eco
Car Electric S.A., and are powered by six or eight rechargeable
batteries capable of running up to seven hours between recharges.
</P>
<P>
The cars can carry two or four persons and reach a speed of 25
miles, or 40 kilometers, per hour.
</P>
<P>
The two bicycles will substitute for the motorcycles in the
parks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
