<HEADLINE> Simitis: Drachmas' Entry Into ERM Useful For Greek </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Greek Prime Minister Costas
Simitis said Saturday night that the drachma's entry into the
European exchange rate mechanism (ERM) would lead the country's
economy to strong development.
</P>
<P>
In his address to the nation shortly after the decision taken
by the European Union member state ministers and central bank
governors to include the Greek national currency into the EU's
ERM, Simitis stressed that this would be able to win increased
international trust and recognition of the prospect of Greece's
entry to the final stage of the European Monetary Union (EMU),
which would allow Greece to participate in the decision-making
processes.
</P>
<P>
He urged the Greek people, just like its European partners, to
trust the decision the government has made.
</P>
<P>
The EU ministers said in a joint communique that the Greek
drachma's new parity to the European currency unit (ECU) as of
Saturday would be at 357.00 drachmas against one ECU.
</P>
<P>
The 14-percent devaluation would fortify the drachma and lead
to lower interest rates, a development which would lower the
national debt and would lead the Greek economy to self-sustaining
growth. 
</P>
</TEXT>
