<HEADLINE> Syrian, Lebanese Presidents Hold Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Syrian President Hafez Al-Assad
Saturday held talks with his Lebanese counterpart Elias Hrawi on
the latest developments in the Middle East region, the Syrian News
Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders said after a series of meetings that the two
countries insisted on the land-for-peace principle.
</P>
<P>
Al-Assad said that Syria will always stand by the Lebanese side
and support its efforts that are beneficial to the country's
national interests, stability and reconstruction.
</P>
<P>
Diplomatic sources here hold that the summit was part of the
Syrian-Lebanese consultations just one week before the arrival of
U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan at the Lebanese capital of
Beirut.
</P>
<P>
Syria and Lebanon are expected to reach a single position on
the necessity of the unconditional withdrawal of the Israeli
troops from south Lebanon according to U.N. resolution 425, which
calls for Israeli pullout from Lebanon without delay.
</P>
<P>
The Lebanese president arrived here Saturday on an official
visit to Syria. 
</P>
</TEXT>
